review_blob:
I am not normaly a cider drinker. In trueth the only reason lm drinking my 2nd pint of it now id due to the fact l liked the name and thought it was an ale.
  Saying that its blooming marvellous! It also leaves an unplaceable after taste l can only liken to mead!
Not an amazing drink but gives a chow mein or jerk pork/chicken a real kick when used in cooking!
Nothing satisfies me like a Bishops finger...or ten! At least in a Sheapered Neame pub anyway.
Half a pint of Special topped off with a bottle of Ram Rod. Honestly I could drink this till the sheep come home!
Half a pint of Youngs Special Brew topped off with a bottle of Youngs Ram Rod, you cant ask for more. Honestly I would and could drink this all day everyday.
Nothing signafies the count down to my festive activities like my first pint of this amazing winter ale. This seasonal beer could only be improved by being available all year round!
